FAN (Faces Along Normals) Plugin is a plugin for Blender 2.64.

It allows you to move faces along individual normal vectors.

INSTALL:

* Download fan.py
* Starts Blender
* Go to File > User Preferences > Addons
* Click on "Install Addon..."
* Select the fan.py file and click on "Install Addon..."
* Localize the "Mesh: Faces Along Normals" in the list of addons and check the checkbox to enable the addon
* Tip: if you want to keep the addon enabled after close and restart Blender, you need to save the user settings (File > Save User settings)

USAGE:

* Select your mesh object
* Enter edit mode (TAB)
* Select the faces to move
* Open the specials menu (W)
* Select Move Faces Along Normals
* Select the Distance in the Tool panel to move the faces
* Tip: extrude the faces without move them (E, ESC), then use the Move Faces Along Normals tool